cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.IT, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with pricing mechanisms and revenue maximization, which are topics commonly studied in game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.DS). The use of discriminatory pricing and the analysis of revenue gaps also suggest a connection to market design (cs.MA) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of bounds and the analysis of regular distributions suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
